The African National Congress (ANC) in KwaZulu Natal has called on law enforcement agencies to arrest the killers of its Ethekwini ward 12 chairperson Thulani Nxumalo. He was gunned down outside his home in Kwandengezi Township west of Durban on Monday night. The motive for the killing is unknown. Nxumalo was also a member of the Community Policing Forum. His death coincides with the expected release of the Moerane commissionâ€™s report into political killings in the province. WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: